<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>TSI 01-16-07 - HVAC Fresh Air Filter, Code 16WKY, used in 4200, 4300, 4400 Models</stitle>
    <tsi id="tsi011607" tsitype="truck">
        <tsinumber>01-16-07</tsinumber>
        <tsidate>December, 2001</tsidate>
        <subjectfile>CAB</subjectfile>
        <subjectgroup>
            <subject>HVAC Fresh Air Filter, Code 16WKY, used in 4200, 4300, 4400 Models</subject>
        </subjectgroup>
        <apply>
            <configure>
                <truckmodelgroup/>

                <truckmodel>4200</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>4300</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>4400</truckmodel>
                <ucodegroup/>

                <ucode>16WKY</ucode>
            </configure>
        </apply>
        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>When a vehicle is ordered and sales code 16WKY is specified, a fresh air filter is installed in
                    the HVAC system which is mounted on the engine side of the cab. As the filter becomes restricted the
                    air flow through the air conditioner evaporator and heater core will be reduced. When this occurs
                    the cooling and heating efficiency of the system will be reduced. The filter should be inspected for
                    dust and road dirt at the beginning of each season and cleaned or replaced as needed.
                </para>
                <para>Vehicles that were not ordered with sales code 16WKY can have the filter added. If a vehicle is
                    operating in a dusty or dirty environment the filter should be added to prevent the air conditioner
                    evaporator or heater core from becoming plugged.
                </para>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
